# Data & Schema Rules

## 2dsphere Index — Required for Geo Queries

Any collection with `$near`, `$geoWithin`, or `$geoIntersects` queries MUST define a `2dsphere` index. Missing index = full collection scan.

```typescript
// Schema field
@Prop({ type: { type: String, enum: ['Point'], default: 'Point' }, coordinates: [Number] })
location: { type: string; coordinates: [number, number] };

// Index — not optional
ProviderSchema.index({ location: '2dsphere' });
```

Flag any geo query added without a corresponding 2dsphere index.

## Compound Indexes — Query First, Schema Second

Design indexes from query patterns before writing the schema, not after.

```typescript
// Provider search: active providers, ordered by geo distance
ProviderSchema.index({ status: 1, location: '2dsphere' });

// Booking lookup: by provider, filtered by status, sorted by date
BookingSchema.index({ providerId: 1, status: 1, scheduledAt: -1 });

// User bookings: by customer, filtered by status
BookingSchema.index({ customerId: 1, status: 1 });
```

## Soft Deletes — Never Hard Delete

Bookings and users are never hard-deleted — they have payment and history ties.

```typescript
@Prop({ type: Date, default: null })
deletedAt: Date | null;
```

Default queries must filter `{ deletedAt: null }`. Use a Mongoose pre-query middleware or global plugin per collection to enforce this — do not rely on call-site filtering.
